5. Cascade Types

Cascade types define what happens to related entities when you perform operations (save,
delete, etc.) on the parent.

ALL: Applies all cascade operations.
PERSIST: Saves related entities when the parent is saved.
MERGE: Merges changes to related entities.
REMOVE: Deletes related entities when the parent is deleted.
REFRESH: Refreshes related entities.
DETACH: Detaches related entities from the persistence context.

Example:

@OneToMany(mappedBy = "user", cascade = CascadeType.ALL)
private List<Post> posts;

If you save or delete a User, all their Posts are also saved or deleted.
